[1] China: National Health Commission, 83 075 total cases, 4634 deaths
Date: Fri 12 Jun 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [abridged, edited]
http://en.nhc.gov.cn/2020-06/13/c_80744.htm


On [12 Jun 2020]:
- 11 new cases of confirmed infection (5 imported cases -- 1 each in Shanghai municipality, Tianjin municipality, Guangdong province, Hainan province and Sichuan province -- and 6 locally acquired cases in Beijing), no new suspected cases and no new deaths. Also, 2 patients were released from hospital after being cured; 635 people who had had close contact with infected patients were freed from medical observation.
- 1808 [total] cases of imported confirmed infections and no deaths.
- The National Health Commission had received reports of 83 075 confirmed cases and 4634 deaths; 78 367 patients had been cured and discharged from hospital; 751 383 people have been identified as having had close contact with infected patients and 3197 are now under medical observation.
- 7 new asymptomatic cases (5 imported); no asymptomatic cases became a confirmed case (imported); 98 asymptomatic cases were still under medical observation (including 48 imported cases).
- 1596 confirmed infections had been reported in the Hong Kong and Macau special administrative regions and Taiwan province: 1108 in Hong Kong, 45 in Macau.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[According to the report above, in the past 24 hours, there have been 11 newly confirmed cases in China, 5 of which were imported and 6 locally acquired -- the latter all in Beijing. No new deaths were reported. Also, 1 new case was reported in Hong Kong, none in Macau. A total of 1808 imported cases have been reported. There have been no new deaths reported for several weeks, further supporting a reduced level of cases in the country.

There were 7 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals in the past 24 hours -- 5 were imported. There were no cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. The recent previous reports of a conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic were on 4, 6, 8, 9, 10 and 11 Jun 2020 when 1 conversion was reported each time. Prior to that, there were 2 cases on 1 Jun 2020, and a single case was reported on 18 May 2020 (COVID-19 update (194): China, S Korea, countries w/ high local trans, Italy phase 2 20200519.7352327).

Recurrent questions: What is the total number of asymptomatic cases? What is the total number of asymptomatic cases that converted to symptomatic? What is the proportion of asymptomatic imported cases that have been linked to transmission chains resulting in outbreak clusters?

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png, and a HealthMap/ProMED map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7464550,155. - Mod.MPP]

