Change: 49 newly confirmed infections; 0 new deaths

[The table with distribution by provinces is available at the source URL above. - Mod.MPP]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the past 24 hours, according to the report at the source URL, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 49 cases and 0 new deaths, compared with 56 cases and 1 new death in the previous day (12 Jun 2020). (Of note, yesterday's report had a total of 12 003 cases, whereas today the report says there were 12 002 cases.) The daily newly confirmed case count has been at or below 100 for 67 consecutive days. Today's (13 Jun 2020) breakdown of cases: 44 cases were locally transmitted, and 5 were imported cases. Locally acquired cases were in Seoul (29), Gyeonggi (13), Incheon (1) and Chungnam (1). Imported cases were in Daegu (3), Gyeonggi (1), and Quarantine (1). Note that 12 provinces did not report any newly confirmed cases.

Updated tables and graphs can be found at Notice 371 https://www.cdc.go.kr/board/board.es?mid=&bid=0030.

The impression (hasn't changed): Lifting of measures has been accompanied by increases in locally acquired infections through increasing clusters related to gatherings of people at employment (bringing it outside employment to contacts) and in houses of worship, and bars and clubs. It just takes one super-spreader in a crowded place to transmit and lead to a sizeable cluster.

A map of South Korea showing provinces can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/korea-south-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7464550,195. - Mod.MPP]

