[4] Iran: 182 545 total cases, 8659 deaths
Date: Fri 12 Jun 2020
Source: The Armenian Reporter [abridged, edited]
https://www.reporter.am/irans-death-toll-from-coronavirus-surges-beyond-8600-middle-east-monitor/


Iran today [12 Jun 2020] confirmed 75 more fatalities from the novel coronavirus in the past 24 hours, bringing the nationwide death toll to 8659. A further 2369 people tested positive for COVID-19, raising the overall case count to 182 545, Health Ministry spokesperson Sima Sadat Lari said.

According to the [spokesperson], 144 649 people have to date recovered and been discharged from hospitals, while 2739 patients remain in a [critical] condition. Some 1.19 million tests have been performed in the country currently, Lari said.

Iran is witnessing an upward trend in daily infections in lots of provinces, particularly in the southwestern Khuzestan province, because of the easing of restrictions on movement. Despite the rising amount of infections, government employees have resumed work, and mosques reopened over the Middle Eastern country. Shopping malls also have reopened.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As of 12 Jun 2020, the total number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran is 182 545, including 8659 deaths, an increase of 2369 new cases and 75 deaths since 11 Jun 2020.

Iran has started relaxing restrictions on a more widespread basis in the country. As stated previously, with the increasing daily case reports having surpassed the prior peak in late March-early April 2020, it is clear that there is now a 2nd wave, most likely due to too early lifting of restrictions. The key concern will be whether people begin travelling again within the country and may transport the virus from one zone to another.

A map of Iran showing provinces can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/iran/iran-political-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7464550,128 - Mod.MPP]

